Que 1)What is CSS? What are the 5 ways to Implement CSS in HTML?
-----------------------------------------------------------------
CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is used to style and design web pages.
It controls things like colors, fonts, layout, spacing, and responsiveness.
5 ways to implement CSS in HTML:
1️⃣ Inline CSS
<p style="color:red;">Hello</p>
2️⃣ Internal CSS
<style>
p { color: red; }
</style>
3️⃣ External CSS
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
4️⃣ @import rule
@import url("style.css");
5️⃣ CSS Frameworks / Libraries
Example: Bootstrap CSS included in HTML.
Que 2) What is Inline Style in CSS? When to use it in real applications?
Inline CSS is written directly inside the HTML tag using the style attribute.
Example:
<p style="color:blue;">Hello</p>
When to use:
Quick testing
Small changes for a single element
Temporary styling
It is not recommended for large projects.
Que 3) What is Internal Stylesheet in CSS? When to use it in real applications?
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Internal CSS is written inside the <style> tag in the <head> section.
Example:
<head>
<style>
p { color: green; }
</style>
</head>
When to use:
Small websites
Single-page applications
Testing styles
Que 4) What is External Stylesheet in CSS? When to use it in real applications?
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
External CSS is written in a separate .css file and linked to HTML.
Example:
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
Example CSS file:
p {
color: red;
}
When to use:
Large websites
Multiple pages
Real-world projects
Que 5) What are the 5 advantages of external stylesheet?
-------------------------------------------------------
1️⃣ Reusable across multiple pages
2️⃣ Cleaner HTML code
3️⃣ Faster page loading (browser caching)
4️⃣ Easier maintenance
5️⃣ Better project organization
Que 6) How do you Include CSS in a webpage or HTML?
----------------------------------------------------
CSS can be included using:
Inline CSS (style attribute)
Internal CSS (<style> tag)
External CSS (<link> tag)
Example:
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
Que 7) How to implement CSS using @import rule?
-----------------------------------------------
The @import rule is used to import another CSS file into a stylesheet.
Example:
@import url("style.css");
It is usually written inside a CSS file or <style> tag.
Que 8) What is CSS Preprocessors? What is SCSS?
------------------------------------------------
CSS Preprocessors are tools that extend CSS with extra features like:
Variables
Nesting
Functions
Mixins
They make CSS more powerful and easier to manage.
SCSS (Sassy CSS) is a popular CSS preprocessor syntax used in Sass.
Example:
$color: red;
p {
  color: $color;
}
Que 9) What are the 3 Types of CSS Preprocessors?
-----------------------------------------------
1️⃣ Sass / SCSS
2️⃣ LESS
3️⃣ Stylus
These preprocessors help developers write cleaner and more maintainable CSS.
